-1122723465.text: "The closest BCL-2 relatives (BCL-X L, BCL-W, MCL-1, A1/BFL -1 and, in humans, BCL-B) promote cell survival, but BAX and BAK (and possibly BOK) instead promote cell death, as do distant relatives termed BH3-only proteins, because their only homology to BCL-2 (or each other) is the BH3 domain, through which they engage multi-BH domain relatives."
